  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Anne W. Weston attended Ralph Waldo Emerson&apos;s lecture. &quot;It was on character &amp; was quite interesting. The house was full two thirds. He attacked the Abolitionists by name in a very vile manner that is supposing he meant us, for all he said applied perfectly to Torrey Colver etc. The idea was that the Abolitionists were spiritual slaveholders &apos;incarnations of the laws of Georgia and Alabama.&apos; He however bore something of a testimony as to Slavery for he spoke of it in company with &apos;fraud&apos; &amp; other acknowledged vices.&quot; Caroline Weston has a letter from Richard Hildreth.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Included is a typed transcript of paragraph 4, from Emerson&apos;s Essay on Character, that is mentioned Anne Warren Weston&apos;s letter.</subfield>
